            <thetext>Really, we want the following in SASL 2.2:

all cyrus username canonicalization happens via plugins.  This should probably
be pretty easy, just add a krb canon_user plugin, and a unix canon_user plugin
if needed.

auxprop lookups happen to get all the group information.  This will require
atleast the following auxprop plugins: unix, afspts, and ldap.

ideally, cyrus shouldn&apos;t have to care about any of this internally, except for
requesting the group list as an auxprop.</thetext>
